WEBVTT



00:00:00.224 --> 00:00:06.368
Well hey there Anionok, happy 4th of July to you all. I sure wish we could be together at Drake Park.

00:00:06.176 --> 00:00:13.248
but as you know it wasn't available this weekend so we're taking the week off before we head to Crescent Lake next Sunday

00:00:13.056 --> 00:00:23.104
for our church-wide day at the lake. I'm looking forward to seeing you all there and if you haven't yet please register online and let us know you're coming so we know how many to cook.

00:00:22.624 --> 00:00:23.744
15 to cook for.

00:00:23.616 --> 00:00:30.112
For this weekend, I wanted to take a quick moment and share a couple thoughts about Independence Day.

00:00:29.952 --> 00:00:35.392
and specifically how we might experience it as followers of Jesus.

00:00:35.264 --> 00:00:45.312
So many of you know that we've been fixing up this old church building at Six and Clay and we've completely gutted and rebuilt the sanctuary but when we got the key

00:00:44.832 --> 00:00:47.328
the keys to the building last year.

00:00:47.232 --> 00:00:53.440
These two flags were prominently displayed on either side of the baptistry.

00:00:53.280 --> 00:01:01.344
the american flag and the christian flag and you've probably seen a similar set up in other churches or christian schools or something.

00:01:01.120 --> 00:01:04.608
um first let me tell you what i like about that.

00:01:04.736 --> 00:01:14.784
and why I assume the congregation that was here before us set up these two flags in the first place. The truth is, as American Christians, we have dual citizens.

00:01:14.304 --> 00:01:15.520
Citizenship.

00:01:15.392 --> 00:01:20.608
We're citizens of the United States and we're citizens of the Kingdom of God.

00:01:20.768 --> 00:01:27.456
But unlike people who have dual citizenship in two different countries and can go back and forth between them,

00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:31.552
We actually live in two places at the same time.

00:01:31.872 --> 00:01:35.552
And this is true of every Christian in the world, and always has been.

00:01:35.456 --> 00:01:44.096
Think about the way Paul starts a bunch of his epistles. He opens his letters saying something like, "To God's holy people in Ephesus..."

00:01:43.968 --> 00:01:46.720
the faithful in Christ Jesus.

00:01:46.752 --> 00:01:49.344
So he's addressing congregations

00:01:49.216 --> 00:01:52.416
That are living in two places at the same time.

00:01:52.384 --> 00:01:56.640
The Ephesian Christians were dual citizens. They were in Ephesus.

00:01:56.576 --> 00:01:59.104
and they were in Christ.

00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:03.552
and this is the same kind of thing that's true for us as american christians.

00:02:03.584 --> 00:02:05.152
Which is all good.

00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:08.672
Until we start noticing some of the ways

00:02:08.512 --> 00:02:12.352
These two places are in conflict with one another.

00:02:12.512 --> 00:02:18.784
that's when dual citizenship gets complicated. So what do you do when the American way?

00:02:18.752 --> 00:02:20.480
and the Jesus way,

00:02:20.704 --> 00:02:22.912
Are headed in different directions.

00:02:23.008 --> 00:02:26.560
What do you do when God and country

00:02:26.592 --> 00:02:29.280
Are in a tug of war for your loyalty.

00:02:29.760 --> 00:02:32.160
What do you do when our nation

00:02:32.096 --> 00:02:35.776
Sets aside a day to celebrate our independence

00:02:36.192 --> 00:02:37.600
But we know

00:02:37.984 --> 00:02:42.272
That the promise of life, liberty, and the pursuit of happiness

00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:47.200
Came with a price tag of millions of native and African lives.

00:02:48.160 --> 00:02:49.344
It's complicated.

00:02:49.760 --> 00:02:52.256
So the 4th of July is tricky for me.

00:02:52.896 --> 00:02:56.672
And if it isn't tricky for you, I want you to think about it.

00:02:56.416 --> 00:02:57.888
A little bit more.

00:02:58.496 --> 00:03:00.224
I love our country.

00:03:00.128 --> 00:03:02.848
And I'm so grateful that I was born here.

00:03:02.752 --> 00:03:05.920
and then I get to live here. I'm proud to be an American.

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:08.640
But I'm a Christian first.

00:03:08.864 --> 00:03:11.616
I pledge allegiance to the flag

00:03:11.776 --> 00:03:13.728
But my first allegiance...

00:03:13.696 --> 00:03:16.896
Will always be to christ in his kingdom.

00:03:16.928 --> 00:03:24.512
Which is why when we gather to worship in our new sanctuary, you're not going to see either of these flags anywhere.

00:03:24.544 --> 00:03:26.848
The church should be the one place

00:03:26.688 --> 00:03:30.944
in all creation where the Lordship of Christ is unopposed.

00:03:31.040 --> 00:03:32.800
so I love you all

00:03:32.608 --> 00:03:33.920
Happy 4th.

00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:36.864
and I will see you next week at the lake.
